Before the rifle there was the clipboard, and the ACNR never lost it: civic councils, normalista circles, the patient enumeration of Guerrero's grievances village by village. Your organizers work alongside his where the two networks touch, careful never to write down whose is whose — a caution the DFS's cartographers find maddening, since it is also the truth. The state calls it all *guerrilla logistics*. Most of it is literacy classes. That, Genaro would say, is the part they should fear.

@el_canje
title: El canje
subtitle: One time only: his method, your names — captured cadres traded out of the state's hands.
